{
  "text": "The treatment of ICP has mainly been symptomatic because the pathophysiology is still unresolved. Phenobarbital, cholestyramine, S-Adenosyl-L-methionine, dexamethasone and ursodeoxycholic acid have been used [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . It has been shown that UDCA causes a significant reduction in liver function tests in ICP [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . [CITATION_7] concluded in the Cochrane collaboration that UDCA significantly improves pruritus and fewer instances of fetal distress/asphyxial events were seen in the UDCA groups when compared with placebo but the difference was not statistically significant [CITATION_8] . Bacq et al. [CITATION_9] found UDCA have a several benefits for mothers, fetuses as well as for newborns.",
  "correct_citation": {
